<paragraph id="8BED53776D59FFB86987B04F4DF8FCBA" blockId="1.[151,615,769,829]" box="[151,429,804,829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
(
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB8698FB04F4D5EFCBA" box="[159,267,804,829]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB869CEB04E4D5EFCBA" box="[222,267,805,829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86807B04F4D07FCBA" box="[279,338,804,829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="12.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="9.0">9–16</number>
; 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB8684EB04E4DF0FCBA" box="[350,421,805,829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="29.0" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="27.0">27–31</number>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED53776D59FFB86987B007483EFB92" blockId="1.[151,1437,876,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Male (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB869F0B0074D09FC02" box="[224,348,876,901]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86830B0064D09FC02" box="[288,348,877,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Yellowish brown with black markings. Disc of vertex with two spots, narrow elongated spot in antennal cavities; two submarginal narrow black bands on inner side of frontoclypeal suture; clypellus and frontoclypeal sulci black. Antennae pale fuscous. Pronotum with two, large, round black spots posteriorly just above hind margin. Two triangular spots at base of scutellum and median impressed line black. Thoracic pleura black. Forewings brownish hyaline. Female color pattern similar to male (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86AC4B097480BFB92" box="[980,1118,1020,1045]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,218,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 36. Habitus, face and female genitalia of new species 27 – 31 female Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 27, 28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 29. Seventh sternite; 30, 31. Second gonapophyses; 32 – 36 female Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 32, 33. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 34. Seventh sternite; 35, 36 Second gonapophyses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242865/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86D04B096480BFB92" box="[1044,1118,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED53776D59FFB869D7B74B4D55FAB2" blockId="1.[151,1437,876,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Head broadly rounded, crown more or less uniform in length. Anterior margin of pronotum not extending beyond eyes. Anteclypeus exceeding facial margin (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86BCBB72F4F4AFBDA" box="[731,799,1092,1117]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86A1FB72E4F4AFBDA" box="[783,799,1093,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus broad with distinct transverse ridges and face with distinct median carina. Frontal suture extending onto vertex, terminating laterad of ocelli (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86DE2B7034911FB06" box="[1266,1348,1128,1153]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86C36B7024911FB06" box="[1318,1348,1129,1153]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ocelli placed anteriorly on face, closer to anterior margin of vertex than to antennal base, distance between eye and ocellus 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB869E0B7DB4D46FB4E" box="[240,275,1200,1225]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="7.5">7.5</number>
x diameter of ocellus. Antennae situated somewhat at level with lower margin of eye in facial view. Scutellum length 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB8684FB7BE4DD7FB6A" box="[351,386,1237,1261]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="0.9">0.9</number>
x length of pronotum and 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86BBEB7BF4E8AFB6A" box="[686,735,1236,1261]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="0.62">0.62</number>
x its width, transverse depression distinct and nearly reaching lateral margin. Pronotum 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB868A4B7924DB0FA96" box="[436,485,1273,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="0.48">0.48</number>
x longer than broad and 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86BE3B7934F43FA96" box="[755,790,1272,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="5.5">5.5</number>
x longer than crown (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86D14B793481DFA96" box="[1028,1096,1272,1297]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86D28B792481DFA96" box="[1080,1096,1273,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewings without appendix (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB8698FB6774CA6FAB2" box="[159,243,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB869C4B6764CA6FAB2" box="[212,243,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34800FC6D59FFB869D7B62B4F28F8AA" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BED53776D59FFB869D7B62B4D8BF9FE" blockId="1.[151,1437,876,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B9268F656D59FFB869D7B62B4D2DFADE" bold="true" box="[199,376,1344,1369]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB868EBB62B4E01FADE" box="[507,596,1344,1369]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86B26B62A4E01FADE" box="[566,596,1345,1369]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with caudal lobe bearing marginal stout microsetae; caudoventral margin oblique, deeply excavated in the middle. Subgenitalplates (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86D0AB60F4839FAFA" box="[1050,1132,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86D5EB60F4839FAFA" box="[1102,1132,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, elongate, subtriangular, fused to valve but fused to each other along basal third, narrowing gradually towards apical one third, subapical area directed outwards; apex rounded; in lateral view, dorsal margin with short scattered hair-like setae. Connective longer than broad. Styles (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86B9EB6BB4E81FA6E" box="[654,724,1488,1513]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86BD4B6BA4E81FA6E" box="[708,724,1489,1513]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, well developed, outer fork rounded and short, bearing scattered setae, inner fork shorter with basal portion strongly curved and apical portion flat. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB8698FB5734CBAF9B6" box="[159,239,1560,1585]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB869F0B5724CBAF9B6" box="[224,239,1561,1585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB869EFB5734D48F9B6" box="[255,285,1560,1585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="16.0">16</number>
), lateral view, Y-shaped, with atrium forming stage at base, shaft compressed, dorsally directed with apical gonopore and without process on caudal margin near apex. Anal collar process (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86D4EB55748F2F9D2" box="[1118,1191,1596,1621]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86D86B55648F2F9D2" box="[1174,1191,1597,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86DA2B556489AF9D2" box="[1202,1231,1597,1621]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="14.0">14</number>
) dorsal view, well developed, sea-horse shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED53776D59FFB869D7B5EF4FB8F962" blockId="1.[151,1437,876,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B9268F656D59FFB869D7B5EF4DD9F91A" bold="true" box="[199,396,1668,1693]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite (
<figureCitation id="13694FF26D59FFB86B4EB5EF4EFBF91A" box="[606,686,1668,1693]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9A41506D59FFB86B8DB5EE4EFBF91A" box="[669,686,1669,1693]" pageId="1" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
